2 SENATE BILL 440
1 (B) THIS SECTION APPLIES ONLY IN ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY.
2 (C) THE COUNTY COUNCIL SHALL ESTABLISH AN OFFICE OF THE
3 INSPECTOR GENERAL IN THE COUNTY.
4 (D) THE COUNTY COUNCIL SHALL:
5 (1) ENACT A LOCAL LAW THAT ESTABLISHES:
6 (I) THE QUALIFICATIONS FOR THE INSPECTOR GENERAL;
7 (II) THE TERM OF OFFICE OF THE INSPECTOR GENERAL;
8 (III) THE POWERS AND DUTIES OF THE OFFICE; AND
9 (IV) ANY OTHER REQUIREMENT THE COUNTY COUNCIL
10 CONSIDERS NECESSARY FOR THE OPERATION OF THE OFFICE; AND
11 (2) INCLUDE IN THE COUNTY’S ANNUAL OPERATING BUDGET
12 PROPOSAL A PROJECTED BUDGET FOR THE OFFICE FOR THE UPCOMING FISCAL
13 YEAR.
14 (E) (1) THERE IS AN OFFICE OF THE INSPECTOR GENERAL ADVISORY
15 BOARD IN THE COUNTY.
16 (2) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (3) OF THIS SUBSECTION, THE
17 ADVISORY BOARD CONSISTS OF SEVEN MEMBERS APPOINTED BY THE COUNTY
18 EXECUTIVE AND SUBJECT TO CONFIRMATION BY THE COUNTY COUNCIL.
19 (3) A MEMBER OF THE ADVISORY BOARD MAY NOT BE AN ELECTED
20 OFFICIAL OR EMPLOYEE OF:
21 (I) THE STATE;
22 (II) THE COUNTY; OR
23 (III) ANY OTHER FEDERAL, STATE, OR LOCAL GOVERNMENT.
24 (4) (I) SUBJECT TO SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS PARAGRAPH, THE
25 ADVISORY BOARD:

SENATE BILL 440 3
1 1. SHALL SELECT AND APPOINT THE INSPECTOR
2 GENERAL; AND
3 2. MAY REMOVE THE INSPECTOR GENERAL ONLY FOR
4 NEGLECT OF DUTY, MALFEASANCE, CONVICTION OF A FELONY, OR OTHER GOOD
5 CAUSE.
6 (II) AN AFFIRMATIVE VOTE OF A MAJORITY OF THE ADVISORY
7 BOARD IS NECESSARY FOR THE SELECTION, APPOINTMENT, OR REMOVAL OF THE
8 INSPECTOR GENERAL.
9 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
10 October 1, 2025.

